{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "This gradient scaling technique can be used with any of the above supernet methods.Parameter-efficient fine-tuning (PEFT) has been of great benefit in fine tuning LLMs.",
    "BitFit [2] updates the bias terms in pre-trained models while freezing the remaining parameters.",
    "LoRA [16] decomposes attention weight gradients into low-rank matrices to reduce the number of trainable parameters.",
    "AdaLoRA [42] and QLoRA [9] further improve LoRA [16].",
    "Note that PEFT allows fine-tuning a base model on a single GPU but does not produce smaller models."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "BitFit [2] updates the bias terms in pre-trained models while freezing the remaining parameters.",
    "LoRA [16] decomposes attention weight gradients into low-rank matrices to reduce the number of trainable parameters.",
    "AdaLoRA [42] and QLoRA [9] further improve LoRA [16]."
